HEADWORD: Refect
<hw>Re*fect"</hw> <pr>(r?*f?kt)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>refectus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>reficere</ets>; pref. <ets>re-</ets>
re- + <ets>facere</ets> to make.]</ety> <def>To restore after hunger or
fatigue; to refresh.</def> <mark>[Archaic]</mark> <rj><au>Sir T.
Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
